<subSubSection id="C3776556ED573833FF78F904FF24F8E6" pageId="518" pageNumber="519" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED573833FF78F904FF24F8E6" blockId="518.[136,778,1567,2070]" pageId="518" pageNumber="519">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED573833FF78F904FEFBF925" bold="true" box="[189,318,1738,1764]" pageId="518" pageNumber="519">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED573833FD1CF904FCCCF922" box="[729,777,1738,1763]" italics="true" pageId="518" pageNumber="519">ovat</emphasis>
(=egg-shaped), referring to the ovate prosome of the new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED573832FF78F8E1FEBBFA34" lastPageId="519" lastPageNumber="520" pageId="518" pageNumber="519" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED573833FF78F8E1FCB8F88B" blockId="518.[136,778,1567,2070]" lastBlockId="518.[810,1452,1567,2070]" pageId="518" pageNumber="519">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED573833FF78F8E1FE06F888" bold="true" box="[189,451,1839,1865]" pageId="518" pageNumber="519">Descriptionoffemale</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED573833FDE0F8FEFD58F88B" box="[549,669,1840,1866]" captionStart="FIGURE 344" captionStartId="517.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[247,1346,210,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@517.[213,1374,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="517" captionText="FIGURE 344. Notoixys ovata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, ventral; B, cephalic region, dorsal; C, cephalic horn; D, urosome, dorsal; E, left caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C, E–G, 0.05 mm; D, 0.1 mm; H–L, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591995/files/figure.png" pageId="518" pageNumber="519">Fig. 344A</figureCitation>
) straight, slightly depressed, 2.11 mm long. Prosome inflated, oval, 1.76 mm long: greatest width of prosome 1.25 mm, at posterior third. Cephalosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED573833FE23F858FD9EF871" box="[486,603,1942,1968]" captionStart="FIGURE 344" captionStartId="517.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[247,1346,210,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@517.[213,1374,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="517" captionText="FIGURE 344. Notoixys ovata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, ventral; B, cephalic region, dorsal; C, cephalic horn; D, urosome, dorsal; E, left caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C, E–G, 0.05 mm; D, 0.1 mm; H–L, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591995/files/figure.png" pageId="518" pageNumber="519">Fig. 344B</figureCitation>
) short, defined from metasome; dorsal cephalic shield with paired lateral horn-like processes (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED573833FEB2F814FE2AF835" box="[375,495,2010,2036]" captionStart="FIGURE 344" captionStartId="517.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[247,1346,210,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@517.[213,1374,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="517" captionText="FIGURE 344. Notoixys ovata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, ventral; B, cephalic region, dorsal; C, cephalic horn; D, urosome, dorsal; E, left caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C, E–G, 0.05 mm; D, 0.1 mm; H–L, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591995/files/figure.png" pageId="518" pageNumber="519">Fig. 344C</figureCitation>
). Metasome lacking any trace of articulation. Free urosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED573833FDF2F832FD74F7D7" box="[567,689,2044,2070]" captionStart="FIGURE 344" captionStartId="517.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[247,1346,210,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@517.[213,1374,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="517" captionText="FIGURE 344. Notoixys ovata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, ventral; B, cephalic region, dorsal; C, cephalic horn; D, urosome, dorsal; E, left caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C, E–G, 0.05 mm; D, 0.1 mm; H–L, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591995/files/figure.png" pageId="518" pageNumber="519">Fig. 344D</figureCitation>
) small, indistinctly 5-segmented; articulations between somites obscure, representedbyweakconstrictionsand faintsuture lines. Genital somite short, characteristically bearing short, broad hood-like flap of cuticle along posterodorsal margin (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED573833FC4BF969FBCEF903" box="[910,1035,1703,1730]" captionStart="FIGURE 344" captionStartId="517.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[247,1346,210,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@517.[213,1374,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="517" captionText="FIGURE 344. Notoixys ovata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, ventral; B, cephalic region, dorsal; C, cephalic horn; D, urosome, dorsal; E, left caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C, E–G, 0.05 mm; D, 0.1 mm; H–L, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591995/files/figure.png" pageId="518" pageNumber="519">Fig. 344B</figureCitation>
). Caudalramus (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED573833FB1EF969FA96F903" box="[1243,1363,1703,1730]" captionStart="FIGURE 344" captionStartId="517.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[247,1346,210,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@517.[213,1374,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="517" captionText="FIGURE 344. Notoixys ovata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, ventral; B, cephalic region, dorsal; C, cephalic horn; D, urosome, dorsal; E, left caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C, E–G, 0.05 mm; D, 0.1 mm; H–L, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591995/files/figure.png" pageId="518" pageNumber="519">Fig. 344E</figureCitation>
) small, shorter than anal somite and about 2.7 times longer than wide (82×31 μm), tapering in distal third, ornamented with several setules; caudal setae not distinguishable from setules.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED573832FC9AF89CFD34FE8E" blockId="518.[810,1452,1567,2070]" lastBlockId="519.[136,778,173,1219]" lastPageId="519" lastPageNumber="520" pageId="518" pageNumber="519">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED573833FC23F89CFBA9F8AD" box="[998,1132,1874,1900]" captionStart="FIGURE 344" captionStartId="517.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[247,1346,210,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@517.[213,1374,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="517" captionText="FIGURE 344. Notoixys ovata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, ventral; B, cephalic region, dorsal; C, cephalic horn; D, urosome, dorsal; E, left caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C, E–G, 0.05 mm; D, 0.1 mm; H–L, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591995/files/figure.png" pageId="518" pageNumber="519">Fig. 344F</figureCitation>
) well-developed, longer than wide, slightly tapering proximally and strongly taperingdistally towards angular apex. Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED573833FABBF858FCAFF813" captionStart="FIGURE 344" captionStartId="517.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[247,1346,210,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@517.[213,1374,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="517" captionText="FIGURE 344. Notoixys ovata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, ventral; B, cephalic region, dorsal; C, cephalic horn; D, urosome, dorsal; E, left caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C, E–G, 0.05 mm; D, 0.1 mm; H–L, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591995/files/figure.png" pageId="518" pageNumber="519">Fig. 344G</figureCitation>
) tapering, 225 μmlong, indistinctly 8-segmented; armatureformula 2, 15, 7, 3, 2, 2, 2, and 7+aesthetasc; third segment subdivided; all setae small, setule-like. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED563832FF3DFF63FEABFF06" box="[248,366,173,199]" captionStart="FIGURE 344" captionStartId="517.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[247,1346,210,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@517.[213,1374,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="517" captionText="FIGURE 344. Notoixys ovata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, ventral; B, cephalic region, dorsal; C, cephalic horn; D, urosome, dorsal; E, left caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C, E–G, 0.05 mm; D, 0.1 mm; H–L, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591995/files/figure.png" pageId="519" pageNumber="520">Fig. 344H</figureCitation>
) 4-segmented; proximal 3 segments unarmed; terminal segment (second endopodal segment) 2.7 timeslongerthan wide (68×25 μm) and longerthan firstendopodal segment: armedwith 7 setae (arranged as 2, 2, and 3) plus terminal claw half as long as segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED563832FF78FE99FE1CFC8C" blockId="519.[136,778,173,1219]" pageId="519" pageNumber="520">
Labrum weak, easily damaged during dissection. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED563832FECBFEB7FE47FE52" box="[270,386,377,403]" captionStart="FIGURE 344" captionStartId="517.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[247,1346,210,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@517.[213,1374,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="517" captionText="FIGURE 344. Notoixys ovata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, ventral; B, cephalic region, dorsal; C, cephalic horn; D, urosome, dorsal; E, left caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C, E–G, 0.05 mm; D, 0.1 mm; H–L, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591995/files/figure.png" pageId="519" pageNumber="520">Fig. 344I</figureCitation>
) with 3 small teeth and short pectinate margin on coxal gnathobase: basis with broad setaon medial margin: exopod with 4 equally large setae and 1 short outer seta half as long as others: endopod with 1 and 6 setae on first and second segments, respectively. Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED563832FEC1FDEDFEAAFDFC" box="[260,367,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 344" captionStartId="517.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[247,1346,210,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@517.[213,1374,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="517" captionText="FIGURE 344. Notoixys ovata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, ventral; B, cephalic region, dorsal; C, cephalic horn; D, urosome, dorsal; E, left caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C, E–G, 0.05 mm; D, 0.1 mm; H–L, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591995/files/figure.png" pageId="519" pageNumber="520">Fig. 344J</figureCitation>
) armedwith 6 setaeon arthrite, 1 on epipodite, 2 on basis, 4 onexopodand 3 on endopod; setae on endopod longer than those on exopod; coxal endite absent. Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED563832FE8CFD47FE04FD62" box="[329,449,649,675]" captionStart="FIGURE 344" captionStartId="517.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[247,1346,210,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@517.[213,1374,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="517" captionText="FIGURE 344. Notoixys ovata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, ventral; B, cephalic region, dorsal; C, cephalic horn; D, urosome, dorsal; E, left caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C, E–G, 0.05 mm; D, 0.1 mm; H–L, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591995/files/figure.png" pageId="519" pageNumber="520">Fig. 344K</figureCitation>
) 5-segmented; syncoxawith 3, 1, 2, and 2 setae on first to fourth endites, respectively; basis with short claw plus 2 unequal setae; endopod with 1, 1, and 2 setae on first to third segments, respectively. Maxilliped (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED563832FEDDFCDFFE4AFCEA" box="[280,399,785,811]" captionStart="FIGURE 344" captionStartId="517.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[247,1346,210,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-18@517.[213,1374,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="517" captionText="FIGURE 344. Notoixys ovata gen. et sp. nov., female.A, habitus, ventral; B, cephalic region, dorsal; C, cephalic horn; D, urosome, dorsal; E, left caudal ramus, dorsal; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C, E–G, 0.05 mm; D, 0.1 mm; H–L, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591995/files/figure.png" pageId="519" pageNumber="520">Fig. 344L</figureCitation>
) as unsegmented, elongate lobe bearing 5 naked setae distally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED563832FF78FC98FF21FB02" blockId="519.[136,778,173,1219]" pageId="519" pageNumber="520">
Legs 1–4 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED563832FE88FC9BFE7DFCB1" box="[333,440,853,880]" captionStart="FIGURE 345" captionStartId="518.[136,245,1431,1457]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,211,1351]" captionTargetId="figure-19@518.[136,1451,185,1366]" captionTargetPageId="518" captionText="FIGURE 345. Notoixys ovata gen. et sp. nov., female. A, leg 1; B, leg 2; C, leg 3; D, leg 4. Scale bars: A, B, 0.05 mm; C, D, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591997" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591997/files/figure.png" pageId="519" pageNumber="520">Fig. 345</figureCitation>
A-D) with incompletely 3- segmented rami. Protopod obscurely segmented in legs 3 and 4. Endopods slightly shorter than exopods in legs 1 and 2, but distinctly shorter, half as long as exopod, in legs 3 and 4. Inner coxal seta present in legs 1 and 2, absent in legs 3 and 4. Setae on rami small, markedly smaller inlegs 3 and 4. First exopodal segments of legs 3 and 4 lacking inner seta. Second endopodal segment of leg 2 bearing 2 inner setae. Second endopodal segment of leg 3 lacking inner seta. Armature formula for legs 1–4 as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED563832FF2DFB23FEF2FA70" pageId="519" pageNumber="520">
