. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED563832FF78FA30FD79F84F" pageId="519" pageNumber="520" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED563832FF78FA30FD9AF925" blockId="519.[136,778,1499,1934]" pageId="519" pageNumber="520">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED563832FF78FA30FEEFF9D9" bold="true" box="[189,298,1534,1560]" pageId="519" pageNumber="520">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED563832FEF2FA30FE19F9D6" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[311,476,1534,1559]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Didemnidae" genus="Notoixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="519" pageNumber="520" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ovata" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED563832FEF2FA30FE19F9D6" box="[311,476,1534,1559]" italics="true" pageId="519" pageNumber="520">Notoixys ovata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED563832FE24FA30FD4EF9D9" bold="true" box="[481,651,1534,1560]" pageId="519" pageNumber="520">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED563832FE24FA30FD4EF9D9" box="[481,651,1534,1560]" pageId="519" pageNumber="520" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can readily be differentiated from its congeners by the following features: the ovoid, slightly depressed body shape, the presence of the posterodorsal hood-like flap on the genital somite, the presence of only 2 setae on the third endopodal segment of the maxilla, the absence of leg 5, and the characteristic setation of legs 1–4.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED563832FF78F925FD79F84F" blockId="519.[136,778,1499,1934]" pageId="519" pageNumber="520">
The new species is superficially similar in body shape to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED563832FF31F8C0FD6CF8E9" authority="Illg &amp; Dudley, 1965" authorityName="Illg" authorityYear="1965" box="[244,681,1805,1832]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Mesoixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="519" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="otaria">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED563832FF31F8C0FE69F8E6" box="[244,428,1806,1831]" italics="true" pageId="519" pageNumber="520">Mesoixys otaria</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED563832FE7DF8C3FD6CF8E9" author="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L." box="[440,681,1805,1832]" journalOrPublisher="Pubblicazioni della Stazione Zoologica di Napoli" pageId="519" pageNumber="520" pagination="373 - 451" part="34" refId="ref329106" refString="Illg, P. L. &amp; Dudley, P. L. (1965) Notodelphyid copepods from the vicinity of Naples. Pubblicazioni della Stazione Zoologica di Napoli, 34, 373 - 451." title="Notodelphyid copepods from the vicinity of Naples" type="journal article" year="1965">Illg &amp; Dudley, 1965</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED563832FF13F8FEFEFBF888" authorityName="Illg &amp; Dudley" authorityYear="1965" box="[214,318,1840,1865]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Mesoixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="519" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED563832FF13F8FEFEFBF888" box="[214,318,1840,1865]" italics="true" pageId="519" pageNumber="520">Mesoixys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED563832FDAEF8FEFD08F888" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[619,717,1840,1865]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Didemnidae" genus="Notoixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="519" pageNumber="520" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
